<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="ru">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>The Difference Between Responsive and Adaptive Design</title>
    <style>
        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #0f514e;
            color: white;
            line-height: 1.6;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding-top: 40px;
        }

        .breadcrumbs {
            font-size: 14px;
            color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .breadcrumbs span {
            margin: 0 5px;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 48px;
            font-weight: 700;
            line-height: 1.2;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
            max-width: 800px;
        }

        .meta-info {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 30px;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            padding-bottom: 40px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
        }

        .author-block {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 12px;
        }

        .avatar {
            width: 40px;
            height: 40px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            background-color: white;
            background-size: cover;
        }

        .author-name {
            font-size: 14px;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        .author-label {
            font-size: 12px;
            display: block;
        }

        .meta-item {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }
        .meta-label {
            font-size: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 2px;
        }
        .meta-value {
            font-size: 14px;
            font-weight: 500;
        }
        .comments-link {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 14px;
            font-weight: 500;
        }
        
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="breadcrumbs">
            Home <span>/</span> Articles <span>/</span>
        </div>

        <h1>The Difference Between Responsive and Adaptive Design</h1>

        <div class="meta-info">
            <div class="author-block">
                <div class="avatar"></div>
                <div>
                    <span class="author-label">Author</span>
                    <span class="author-name">Geoff Graham</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="meta-item">
                <span class="meta-label">49 Comments</span>
                <a href="#" class="comments-link">Go to comments</a>
            </div>

            <div class="meta-item">
                <span class="meta-label">Published</span>
                <span class="meta-value">Nov 11, 2018</span>
            </div>

            <div class="meta-item">
                <span class="meta-label">Updated</span>
                <span class="meta-value">Nov 17, 2018</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>

